    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-24T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-24T13:00:00-05:00" n="305"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d305">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/979</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Christiania</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-24T19:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.37 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1277. From <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_OWH1">Owen</persName> to War
                    Trade Board:</p>
                <p>No. 168. Draft of corkmakers’ benevolent [<hi rend="italic">branch</hi>]
                    agreement approved by you in Department’s No. 436, August 24, 5 p.m., No. 52 for
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DAV1">Dye</persName>, is not in
                    accordance with instructions in Department’s 396, July 26, 4 p.m. Other branch
                    arrangements are being drawn up in the same manner as corkmakers’ agreement.
                    Should not the words “War Trade Board” be substituted for “United States
                    Government” in first paragraph of these draft agreements, and should the term
                    Associated Governments be employed through these forms?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Schmedeman</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
